Nothing in this Agreement shall be deemed to constitute any Owner as a partner of, or joint venturer with, any other Owner. The employees, agents, and subcontractors of the Owners, in performing the obligations of each respective Owner under this Agreement, shall not be deemed to be the agents or employees or subcontractors of any other Owner. Each Owner acknowledges that while the Owners may hold certain undivided interests in the Common Real Property Documents, and as such, all Owners would be entitled to control the Common Real Property Documents and their use, each Owners right to occupy and use the Common Premises is governed by and subject to this Agreement. 13.2 Regulatory Approvals and Assurances . Each Party acknowledges and agrees that the use of the electrical transmission lines, conductors, insulators and other equipment for the circuits that will serve the Projects and are included in the Common Facilities under this Agreement as well as the payments contemplated under Section 3.1 of this Agreement may constitute the provision of electric service under the Federal Power Act. As of the Effective Date, each Owner and the Common Facilities are eligible for the waiver in 18 C.F.R. § 35.28(d)(2) of the FERC regulations. After the Effective Date, if required by FERC the Owners agree to cooperate with each other to file this Agreement with FERC for review, approval, or acceptance. 13.3 Term and Termination . The term of this Agreement (the Term) shall commence as of the Effective Date and, except for terms that expressly survive the termination of this Agreement, shall terminate upon the first to occur of: (i) a single Owner becoming the Owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Common Assets following the Effective Date, or (ii) the mutual agreement of all the Owners. For FERC filing purposes, this Agreement shall become effective on the later to occur of (a) the Effective Date or (b) the effective date designated by FERC when this Agreement is accepted for filing by FERC. This Agreement shall only be terminated as provided in this Section 13.3. 13.4 Abandonment or Decommissioning of a Project . After the Effective Date, in addition to the obligations of the surrendering Owner set forth in Section 8.3 and in the event an Owner desires to decommission and abandon its Operating Project, and the Common Facilities Ownership Percentage of such Owner are not accepted or the obligations under this Agreement of the surrendering Owner are not assumed by another Owner in writing, the surrendering Owner shall, upon notice to the other Owner(s) of its intent to abandon its Operating Project, be responsible for its proportionate share (as determined by such Owners Proportionate Share as of the date notice of intent to abandon and decommission its Operating Project is given to the other Owners) of the costs and expenses of the removal and wind-up of the Common Assets and the restoration of the Common Premises as required by the Common Real Property Documents (collectively, the Withdrawal Costs). The Common Assets Manager shall administer the calculation, collection, and distribution of the Withdrawal Costs, as follows (provided, however, that if the Common Assets Manager is the surrendering Owner, then the non-surrendering Owner(s) shall have the rights and perform the obligations of the Common Assets Manager under this Section 13.4): (a) The Common Assets Manager shall calculate the Withdrawal Costs and shall provide written notice of same to the surrendering Owner within forty-five (45) days after the Common Assets Manager has received notice of Owners intent to abandon its Project. (b) The surrendering Owner shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the written notice of the Withdrawal Costs, pay the Withdrawal Costs to the Manager. The Withdrawal Costs shall be maintained by the Common Assets Manager in a reserve account and used by the Common Assets Manager for removal of the Common Assets and the restoration of the Common Premises when same becomes necessary. (c) Upon any failure to pay the Withdrawal Costs constituting a default hereunder, the applicable Owner shall automatically forfeit all of its Common Facilities Ownership Percentage hereunder to the other Owner(s) and shall immediately cease and desist from the use of the Common Assets. The surrendering Owner further irrevocably appoints the Common Assets Manager as its true and lawful attorney, with full power of substitution, for the sole use and benefit of the remaining Owners, but at the surrendering Owners expense, to the extent permitted by law to exercise, at any time and from time to time while the surrendering Owners default has occurred and is continuing, the power to sell, transfer, assign or otherwise deal in or with the Common Facilities Ownership Percentage of the surrendering Owner or the proceeds thereof, as fully and effectually as if the Common Assets Manager were the absolute Owner thereof, provided that the Common Assets Manager shall give to the surrendering Owner not less than ten (10) days prior written notice of the time and place of a sale or other intended transfer or disposition of any of such Common Facilities Ownership Percentage. Any Common Facilities Ownership Percentage of the surrendering Owner transferred or surrendered to the other Owner(s) shall be allocated to each remaining Owner on a pro rata basis in accordance with each remaining Owners Common Facilities Ownership Percentage. 13.5 Distributions . All insurance proceeds from insurance maintained pursuant to Section 7.1, condemnation awards, proceeds from the disposition of assets (reduced by all out-of-pocket costs and expenses reasonably incurred in connection therewith), liquidated damage payments and other payments, credits and refunds received, in each case, attributable to the Common Assets (but excluding payments, credits and refunds received under the Interconnection Agreement) shall be used by the Common Assets Manager to repair or replace the Common Assets or, if not applicable, shall be distributed to the Owners in proportion to their respective Common Facilities Ownership Percentage. 13.6 Distribution on Termination of this Agreement . In the event that the Owners decide to decommission all of the Projects and to proceed with the removal of the Common Assets, the Common Assets Manager shall take account of all the Owners joint assets covered by this Agreement, including the Common Assets, and joint liabilities pursuant to this Agreement and shall proceed with the liquidation thereof. The assets covered by this Agreement shall be liquidated under the supervision of the Common Assets Manager as promptly as is consistent with obtaining a reasonable value therefor, and the proceeds therefrom, together with any assets distributed in- kind, shall be applied and distributed as follows: (a) To the payment of debts and liabilities of the Owners to third parties in connection with the Common Assets which are then due and the expenses of liquidation. (b) To the setting up of any reserves which the Common Assets Manager deems reasonably necessary for any contingent or unforeseen liabilities or obligations or debts not yet payable by the Owners in connection with the Common Assets, including any reserves to pay costs associated with the decommissioning and removal of the Common Assets. (c) Any sum remaining shall be distributed on a pro rata basis based upon each Owners Common Facilities Ownership Percentage as of the date of final termination of this Agreement. (d) The Common Assets Manager shall have the right, in order to effectuate the liquidation of the assets covered by this Agreement to disconnect the Common Assets from the Projects. 13.7 Uncontrollable Forces . No Owner shall be considered to be in default under this Agreement or in breach of this Agreement on account of any failure in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than obligations of such Owner to make any payments that are due and owing pursuant to this Agreement, if failure of such performance is due to the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event. Force Majeure Event, as used herein, means any act or event that delays or prevents an Owner from timely performing all or a portion of its obligations under this Agreement or from complying with all or a portion of the conditions under this Agreement if such act or event, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and is beyond the reasonable control of, and without the fault or negligence of, the Owner relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance, or noncompliance. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, so long as the following events, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and are beyond the reasonable control of, and without the fault or negligence of, the Owner relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance and noncompliance, Force Majeure Events may include: epidemics or pandemics, acts of God; actions of the elements such as heavy rains, floods, earthquakes, hurricanes, tornadoes, lightning, ice storms, landslides, mudslides, flood, subsurface or other site conditions (including environmental contamination, archaeological or other protected cultural resources, and endangered species or protected habitats); explosion; fire; sabotage; terrorism; transportation delays; unavailability of materials; an act of public enemy; war; blockade; civil insurrection; riot; civil disturbance or strike or other labor difficulty caused or suffered by an Owner or any third Person beyond the reasonable control of such Owner (or third Owner) or its Affiliates (even if such difficulties could be resolved by conceding to the demands of a labor group); system emergencies affecting a Project; or any restraint or restriction imposed by Applicable Law or any directive from a Governmental Authority, which by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with Applicable Law an Owner could not reasonably have been expected to avoid and to the extent which, by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with Applicable Law, has been unable to overcome (so long as the affected Owner has not applied for or assisted such act by a Governmental Authority). Any Owner or Common Assets Manager rendered unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of a Force Majeure Event shall give notice of such Force Majeure Event promptly to each of the Owners and shall exercise due diligence to remove such inability and thereafter resume performance with all reasonable dispatch. 13.8 Run With the Land . The Parties hereby agree that all of the covenants, consents and agreements contained in this Agreement touch and concern the subject of the Common Real Property Documents and are expressly intended to, and shall, to the extent allowed by law, be covenants running with the land and shall be binding and a burden upon each Owners present or future estate in the Common Assets and upon each of the Parties hereto from time to time, their respective successors and assigns as holders of an estate or interest in such real estate (including any Lender or other Person acquiring title from any such Person upon foreclosure or by deed in lieu of foreclosure), and shall benefit the Parties hereto from time to time and their respective successors and assigns. To the extent any of the provisions of this Agreement are not enforceable as covenants running with the land, they shall be enforceable as equitable servitudes to the extent allowed by Applicable Law. 13.9 Estoppel Certificates . Upon the request of an Owner, any Lender or the Common Assets Manager, any other Owner and/or the Common Assets Manager, upon not less than ten (10) Business Days notice, shall, if true, provide a certificate stating that (i) this Agreement is in full force and effect and has not been modified or amended (or if modified or amended, stating so), and (ii) to the actual knowledge of the certifying Owner and/or the Common Assets Manager, there are no defaults under this Agreement and no events that, with notice or the passage of time or both, could become a default (or if there are defaults, describing them in reasonable detail). The requesting Owner, and any purchaser, investor or Lender with respect to such Owners portion of the Common Assets, shall be entitled to rely on the truthfulness of the statements made by the certifying Owner or Common Assets Manager in such certificate. The failure of the non-requesting Owner or Common Assets Manager to deliver any such certificate within such time shall be conclusive upon such non-requesting Owner or Common Assets Manager that (a) this Agreement and the rights granted hereunder are in full force and effect and have not been modified and (b) there are no uncured defaults hereunder. 13.10 Partition Waiver . In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Common Assets and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or Owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Article 8 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights as set forth in Section 9.6(c). 13.11 Amendments . This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties; provided, however, that an Owner may amend the Exhibits hereto but only if such amendments or modifications could not reasonably be expected to adversely impact any other non-consenting Owners and could not reasonably be expected to materially reduce the rights or remedies of a Lender or impair or reduce the security for a Lenders lien. Following any amendment to the Exhibits hereto the Owner(s) approving such amendment will promptly deliver a fully executed copy of such amendment to the other Parties hereto as well as a written description of the reason for the amendment and such Parties certification that the amendment complies with the terms of this Section 13.11. For purposes of clarification, transfers or assignments otherwise permitted hereunder shall not be deemed amendments to this Agreement. 13.12 Further Assurances . The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably requested by the Parties to implement this Agreement so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement. 13.13 Condemnation . If all or part of the Common Assets is proposed to be taken as a result of any action or proceeding in eminent domain, or is proposed to be transferred in lieu of condemnation to any authority entitled to exercise the power of eminent domain (collectively, a Taking), Common Assets Manager or any other Owner receiving notice shall provide the other Owner(s) (and if not originally in receipt of the notice, the Common Assets Manager) with reasonable advance notice of any impending proceeding or meeting related to such Taking and shall not in the absence of all parties, or approval of the Owners Committee, settle with the Taking authority or agree on compensation for such Taking. This Agreement shall terminate as to any portion of the Common Assets so condemned or taken (except in the case of a temporary Taking after the duration of which the Owners Committee desires to continue the Agreement, and the Agreement Term shall be extended, in such event, by the duration of such temporary Taking). Any award or other compensation payable as a consequence of such Taking shall be paid according to each Owners Common Facilities Ownership Percentage as described herein. 13.14 Partial Invalidity . Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by FERC or a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall this Agreement continue for a term that is longer than the longest periods permitted by Applicable Law. 13.15 No Third Party Beneficiaries . Except with respect to the rights of an Indemnifying Owner, Lenders and the Common Assets Manager (if not an Owner) as set forth herein, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto and their respective successors and permitted assigns and shall not be construed as benefiting any Person that is not an Owner.
13.16 Entire Agreement; Multiple Counterparts . This Agreement, including the Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto (all of which are incorporated herein by this reference), contains the entire agreement between the Parties hereto in connection with any matter mentioned or contemplated herein, and all prior or contemporaneous proposals, agreements, understandings and representations, whether oral or written, are merged herein and superseded hereby. This Agreement may be executed in multiple counterparts and delivered electronically (including via fax or PDF), all of which counterparts shall together constitute one and the same Agreement.
